text: Maidstone West railway station is one of three railway stations which serve Maidstone in Kent. It is on the Medway Valley Line. == Services == Train services at Maidstone West are run by Southeastern, They use and EMUs. The off-peak service is: * 2 trains per hour to * 2 trains per hour to Some trains go to . Two high speed services run to and from London St Pancras International.
